summary: “And so, the new Iron Man, champion of champions, is born!” First appearance of the gold & red armor, and first—and longest, I...
caption:
“And so, the new Iron Man, champion of champions, is born!”

First appearance of the gold & red armor, and first—and longest, I believe—instance of the classic fetishistic reverse striptease transformation sequence. 

Tales of Suspense #48, December 1963, written by Stan Lee, art by Steve Ditko and Dick Ayers 

(Iron-Man first appeared in TOS #39, March 1963—it took Stan nine months to get rid of the clumsy, tank-like original armor and steer the character’s design into the more organic one we’re used to, but it was well worth the wait.)
